# Solaris-III Lore: Metaphysics and Phenomena

<!-- Sources: https://wutheringwaves.fandom.com/wiki/The_Lament, https://wutheringwaves.fandom.com/wiki/Waveworn_Phenomenon, https://wutheringwaves.fandom.com/wiki/Etheric_Sea, https://wutheringwaves.fandom.com/wiki/Remnant, https://wutheringwaves.fandom.com/wiki/Resonator -->

## Solaris-III: Metaphysics — Frequency and Reality

- **Fundamental Law:** Reality on Solaris-III is constructed of **frequencies**. Matter, energy, biological life, and even memory are quantifiable as vibrational data.
- **Manipulation:** This ontological framework allows for **Resonance** — the ability to manipulate reality by synchronizing with these frequencies.
- **Sound as Building Block:** Sound and vibration are not just sensory inputs but the "source code" of the physical world. This is why phenomena are named with auditory terms (Lament, Threnodian, Echo, Tacet, Reverberation).

## The Lament: Definition and Nature

- **The Lament** (Chinese: 悲鸣, literally "wail of sorrow") is the official classification for all major catastrophic mass-extinction events and disaster trends that have affected Solaris-III.
- It is not a single event but a **recurring, systemic phenomenon** — a cycle of destruction and destabilization whose ultimate origin remains unknown, though certain scholars and the Fractsidus believe an entity called **"The Shepherd"** may be behind the earliest Lament.
- The Lament disrupts the **fundamental laws of physics**, with gravity being described as the only force that remains consistently unaltered. All other physical constants — electromagnetism, thermodynamics, causality — become unreliable during active Lament events.
- As described in _Chapter I: Act VIII — To the Shore's End_, this destabilization causes reality itself to fracture unpredictably: terrains warp, time-displaced echoes of past events manifest, and both natural and man-made systems fail.
- The Shorekeeper describes the Lament as _"the death knell for humanity, leaving billions upon billions of lives lost to its wail."_
- The Lament has a **psychological dimension** as well: exposure to its energies induces obsessive behavior, hallucinations, and emotional instability — particularly despair, grief, and fixation on past traumas. These effects stem from **Remnant Energy** interacting with human consciousness, creating feedback loops of unresolved emotion (referenced in the quest _Legacy of the Lasting Night_).
- The Lament is classified into **global Laments** (planetary-scale extinction events) and **regional Laments** (localized disasters affecting specific areas or nations). Both are tracked and archived by the Black Shores.

## The Lament: Its Role in Shaping Humanity

- Despite its destructive nature, the Lament is also responsible for **humanity's greatest adaptations**. The same chaotic frequency energy that destroys civilization also gave rise to **Resonators** — human beings with the ability to perceive, manipulate, and weaponize frequencies.
- The Lament's residual energy — **Remnant Energy** — is the foundational substrate of almost all supernatural phenomena on Solaris-III, from Tacet Discords to Echoes to the Etheric Sea itself.
- The Lament physically isolated Solaris-III from the rest of the universe by filling the sky with the Etheric Sea, ending all interstellar travel and communication. This isolation also means that, even if the Lament has cosmic origins, Solaris cannot seek outside help.
- Sociologically, the recurring Lament has shaped every nation's culture, religion, military doctrine, and governance structure. In **Huanglong**, it drove the creation of military forces like the Midnight Rangers. In **Rinascita**, it led to the establishment of the religious Order of the Deep. In **Lahai-Roi**, it drove the Roya underground and into collaboration with the Exostrider.
- The **Fractsidus** views the Lament not as a catastrophe to be stopped but as a necessary evolutionary pressure. They call the ultimate Lament they plan to trigger the **"True Lament"** — a total event meant to push humanity to its final form, whatever that may be.

## The Etheric Sea: The Sealed Sky

- The **Etheric Sea** is a planet-wide phenomenon born from an anomalous Lament event — a vast expanse of extremely high-density **Remnant Energy** that now blankets Solaris-III's atmosphere like an inverted ocean.
- Visually, the sky in areas affected by the Etheric Sea's direct presence appears to resemble an upside-down ocean surface — a surreal and distinctive feature of the Wuthering Waves world.
- The Etheric Sea did not form all at once; its expansion was gradual enough that the **Court of Savantae** was able to launch the **SkyArk Space Station** to study it in the early Post-Lament period before the sky was fully sealed.
- The Etheric Sea has rendered all forms of interstellar or even orbital travel impossible. Its extreme Remnant Energy density disrupts the functioning of **Pangu Terminals** and other advanced technology when concentrated.
- It serves as the source of the **Retroact Rain** phenomenon: condensed droplets of Remnant Energy fall from the Sea and cause time-distorted hallucinations on the ground below.
- Wherever the Etheric Sea converges with the surface — particularly where it "lowers" toward the ground — new **Tacet Fields** form. This makes it both a passive environmental hazard and an active generator of Tacet Discord activity.
- The Etheric Sea is a massive attractor for Tacet Discords, meaning areas where it is most visible or active are always the most heavily infested.
- Research suggests the Etheric Sea is composed of **Remnant Energy** — the same data-like residues of memory and emotion left behind by all living things and events that have passed through the Lament.

## Waveworn Phenomenon: Overview and Classification

- **Waveworn Phenomenon** (Chinese: 海蚀现象, literally "Coastal/Sea Erosion Phenomenon") is the collective term for all anomalous occurrences caused directly by the influence of the Lament on Solaris-III.
- These phenomena range in scale from minor localized distortions to full ecological and psychic collapse of entire regions. Their defining characteristic is their chaotic, unpredictable nature and their association with Tacet Discords.
- The name reflects the "erosive" effect the Lament has on Solaris-III — an erosion that is not merely physical but **metaphysical**, distorting memory, structure, and causality itself.
- The Waveworn Phenomenon is believed to operate by altering matter, information, and energy, converting them all into vibrating **"frequencies."** The decaying remnants of this conversion process are called **Reverberations**.
- Academically, the Waveworn Phenomenon is an active area of research at institutions like **Huaxu Academy** (Huanglong) and **Startorch Academy** (Lahai-Roi), though the full picture of its mechanism remains incomplete.
- Key identified types of Waveworn Phenomenon include: **Tacet Discord Outbreaks**, **Tacet Fields**, **Retroact Rain**, **Gravitational Anomalies**, the **Dark Tide**, the **Void Storm**, and **Irideglow Crystal** formation.

## Waveworn Phenomenon: Tacet Discord Outbreaks

- **Tacet Discord Outbreaks** (commonly abbreviated **TD Outbreaks**) are the most frequently occurring and widely known Waveworn Phenomenon.
- They refer to mass emergences of **Tacet Discords** — frequency-based entities that arise from Tacet Fields and spread outward, attacking human settlements and consuming the frequencies of other living things.
- TD Outbreaks are one of the primary threats that every nation on Solaris-III must contend with on a near-constant basis. They form the backbone of military threats faced by organizations like the Midnight Rangers and the Order of the Deep.
- Outbreaks can be intensified dramatically by the presence of a **Threnodian**, which can coordinate and amplify Tacet Discord forces, turning a standard infestation into an extinction-level military event (as seen during the Battle Beneath the Crescent with **Ovathrax**).
- The **Black Shores** monitors TD Outbreak patterns globally through the Tethys System and deploys agents called **Bloom Bearers** to contain the most dangerous outbreaks.

## Waveworn Phenomenon: Tacet Fields

- **Tacet Fields** are geographic Waveworn Phenomena — fixed locations where the Etheric Sea has converged with the surface and created a zone of intense Remnant Energy activity.
- They are visually distinctive: the sky above them shows the inverted-ocean appearance of the Etheric Sea, and a large **cross-shaped Tacet Mark** is stamped deep into the terrain. **Tacetite** formations erupt from the ground around the mark.
- Tacet Fields exhibit localized gravitational distortions — floating debris, warped terrain, and unpredictable spatial behavior. Notable examples include **Qichi Village** and the **Gorges of Spirits** in Huanglong.
- These zones are widely believed to be the **origin point of all Tacet Discords**: entities emerge from the Field's Reverberations and spread outward. **Resonance Cords** — white, glowing filaments — connect the Field to an unknown transdimensional space.
- Tacet Fields begin in a **Dormant phase** of relative stability before becoming active. During dormant periods, the area still attracts Tacet Discords that linger at its perimeter. Retroact Rain events are also more common near active Fields.
- The Tethys System and Resonance Beacons allow the Black Shores to monitor new Field formations in real time.

## Waveworn Phenomenon: Retroact Rain

- **Retroact Rain** is a Waveworn Phenomenon composed of condensed Remnant Energy originating from the Etheric Sea, first depicted in _Chapter I: Act V — Rewinding Raindrops_.
- Due to Remnant Energy's inherent property of **recording events across time and space**, exposure to the rain triggers vivid illusions of past events — essentially, the rain "plays back" moments from history that were absorbed into the Etheric Sea.
- Individuals with strong emotional ties to the affected location are significantly more susceptible to intense hallucinations. The visions are not passive — they can be psychologically destabilizing.
- Retroact Rain manifests in **three distinct stages**: first as normal-looking rain; then as droplets that appear frozen in mid-air; and finally as droplets that fall **upward**, in apparent reversal of gravity.
- While generally non-lethal, Retroact Rain is a potent attractor for Tacet Discords due to its high Remnant Energy concentration. A **Threnodian's presence** can dramatically amplify its effects — as witnessed during the Battle Beneath the Crescent when **Ovathrax** enhanced the Retroact Rain to project deadly phantoms of both fallen soldiers and monsters.
- Crucially, the frequencies of any individual who **dies within Retroact Rain** are permanently embedded into the rain itself — meaning every instance carries a growing record of the dead.

## Waveworn Phenomenon: Gravitational Anomalies

- Gravitational anomalies are among the most physically dramatic manifestations of the Waveworn Phenomenon. The Lament's disruption of natural physics causes localized zones where gravity behaves erratically.
- Notable examples include areas within **Qichi Village**, the **Port City of Guixu**, **Norfall Barrens**, and the vicinity of **Avinoleum** in Rinascita — all showing floating debris, inverted terrain structures, or objects suspended in mid-air.
- Despite the Lament's disruption of virtually all other physical constants, Chapter III of the main story reveals that **gravity itself is the one universal law that was never fully altered** — even the most severe Lament events leave gravity partially functional.
- This is why gravitational anomalies are localized distortions rather than a planet-wide inversion of physics: gravity is bent and warped in Waveworn zones, but is never fully eliminated.
- In **Avinoleum** (Rinascita's Sonoro Sphere), inverted gravity caused by Waveworn activity prevents the **Dark Tide** from descending into the lower Rinascitan cityscape, ironically acting as a natural containment barrier.

## Waveworn Phenomenon: The Dark Tide (Rinascita)

- The **Dark Tide** is a Waveworn Phenomenon native to the region of **Rinascita**, and is the specific catastrophic event most feared by its people. It manifests as a dark, swirling mass of clouds that gathers overhead and eventually breaks open, pouring downward in torrents like a dark waterfall.
- Wherever the Dark Tide strikes, it **spawns Tacet Discords** and converts the area of its origin into a new Tacet Field.
- The first Dark Tide in Rinascita's history was brought about by early theological wars between the settlers who opposed each other over faith in **Leviathan** versus faith in **Imperator** — the conflict of competing divine loyalties literally catalyzed the disaster.
- The Dark Tide was stopped twice in Rinascita's recorded history: the **first time** by **Napoli II**, the first Primus of the Order, using a Lantern given by Imperator; the **second time** by the martyrdom of the Blessed Maiden **Fleurdelys**.
- The Dark Tide functions as a **mechanism of mass assimilation** used by Threnodian Leviathan. Its spread begins through direct contact, converting organic life into hollowed vessels that emit continuous hymns. These transformed entities spread psychological contagion, eventually drawing corrupted souls toward a central convergence called the **"Journeying Paradise."**
- Leviathan's champion **Cartethyia** describes the Dark Tide as a form of "Paradise" — cessation of suffering, hunger, sorrow, and desolation — but this idealized framing masks its true nature as mass subjugation.
- Within **Avinoleum's Sonoro Sphere**, the inverted gravity significantly restrains the Dark Tide's destructive properties, keeping its waters unnaturally calm and navigable by gondola. Residual manifestations still appear as purple-hued vines and flowers that propagate across the landscape.

## Waveworn Phenomenon: The Void Storm (Lahai-Roi)

- The **Void Storm** is a recurring Waveworn Phenomenon unique to the **Lahai-Roi** region, analogous in regional significance to the Dark Tide in Rinascita and the Retroact Rain in Huanglong.
- The Void Storm takes the form of a catastrophic environmental event that periodically cuts off Lahai-Roi from the rest of the world, **blocking all frequencies** moving to and from the region — making communication and travel practically impossible during active events.
- It is associated with **Threnodian Aleph-1**, which arrived in Lahai-Roi during the second global Lament alongside the Exostrider. The Void Storm represents Aleph-1's influence on the local Waveworn environment.
- During the Version 3.0 Cinematic Short, the Void Storm was depicted as manifesting around a **giant Mechanical Wyrm**, triggering all available defense protocols in the region simultaneously.
- The Void Storm's electromagnetic and frequency-blocking properties make it one of the most strategically dangerous regional phenomena, effectively isolating an entire nation during each occurrence.
- The **Exostrider** serves as Lahai-Roi's primary protection against the Void Storm and Aleph-1, functioning as a Sentinel Analog despite not being an officially designated Sentinel.

## Waveworn Phenomenon: Irideglow Crystal (Honami / Ashinohara)

- **Irideglow Crystal** is a Waveworn Phenomenon unique to the city of **Honami** (located in the **Ashinohara** region). It manifests as a crystalline contamination that can trap objects, individuals, and even entire structures in a state of frozen suspension.
- Once solidified, Irideglow is capable of **cutting through and confusing space**, capturing and devouring anything it contacts. It grows in ways that defy conventional spatial understanding.
- Resonators with long-term exposure to Irideglow face an elevated risk of **losing control of their Resonance power** and potentially entering a state of **Overclocking** — an extremely dangerous condition where their abilities spiral beyond their capacity to manage.
- Mildly corrupted Irideglow Crystals can be separated using certain methods, freeing the original object trapped within. Fully crystallized entities, however, are far more difficult to restore.
- Tacet Discords affected by Irideglow become **simultaneously stronger and berserk**, going into an uncontrolled rage upon crystallization. **Chisa** theorizes this is because the Irideglow causes them to reject outsiders; this was later confirmed through the **Chronorift Yakujin**, which used Irideglow contamination to control local TDs and prevent anyone from entering Honami City, treating it as its territory.
- The phenomenon is suspected to be connected to the **Sonoro Sphere of Honami City**, which was sucked into an anomalous space — a significant and ongoing Waveworn disaster.

## Remnant Energy: The Fabric of Frequency

- **Remnant** (also called **Remnant Energy**) is the foundational metaphysical substance of the Wuthering Waves world — described as a "pure and complete form of frequency energy" whose recorded information transcends time and space to exist in a stable form.
- Every event, every life, every emotional experience on Solaris-III produces Remnant Energy. It is, in essence, the universe's record-keeping medium — the substrate on which memory, feeling, and history are encoded.
- The **Etheric Sea** is composed of extremely condensed Remnant Energy. The **Retroact Rain** is condensed Remnant Energy falling from the Etheric Sea. **Tacet Fields** form where Remnant Energy concentrates at the surface. **Tacetite** is a substance that can permanently hold Remnant Energy in a stable material form.
- **Sonoro Spheres** (Chinese: 索诺拉) are transdimensional spaces where Remnant Energy is particularly abundant. They serve as rich historical archives for scholars, because the Remnant within them still carries vivid imprints of past events. The Sonoro Sphere in **Avinoleum** is a major example.
- The **Shorekeeper** is described as an entity composed of high-purity Remnant Energy crystals — effectively a living concentration of this substance.
- Remnant Energy is distinct from **Reverberation**: once Remnant begins to decay, it becomes a Reverberation. This transition is irreversible. Reverberations continue to decay further until they either dissipate entirely or stabilize into **Echoes** through a rare process.

## Reverberation and Echoes: The Decay Cycle

- **Reverberation** is the decayed form of Remnant Energy — the frequency-based residue left behind after matter, information, or living beings have been converted by Waveworn activity.
- The Waveworn Phenomenon converts matter, information, and energy into vibrating "frequencies." The leftover frequency energy from this conversion that continues to slowly decay is classified as Reverberation.
- According to research observations, the transition from Remnant to Reverberation is **irreversible** — once Remnant begins to decay, it cannot be restored to its original state.
- Reverberations acquire a shape as they decay, with the shape varying based on the original frequency's nature — that is, based on how the original source "vibrated." This is conceptually borrowed from **String Theory**, suggesting the developers intended a physics-informed metaphysics.
- A **Tacet Core** (also known academically as a **Reverberation Body**) is the unique structure found in every Tacet Discord — it is essentially a stable concentration of Reverberation that forms the Discord's "core identity."
- **Echoes** are Reverberations that did not fully decay after the death or defeat of a Tacet Discord. Instead of dissipating, they stabilize into a snapshot — a "reverberation photograph" of the Discord's frequencies at the moment of death.
- Echoes can be absorbed through the **Pangu Terminal's Data Bank** and equipped by Resonators to enhance their combat abilities, granting access to the abilities and elemental affinities of the defeated Discord. This system forms one of the game's core gameplay mechanics.
- Echoes are classified into four ranks: **Common**, **Elite**, **Overlord**, and **Calamity** — corresponding to the rank of the TD from which they were obtained.

## Tacetite: Crystallized Frequency

- **Tacetite** is a rare substance discovered through the study of Waveworn Phenomena. Its defining property is the ability to **permanently hold Remnant Energy** in a stable material form, unlike organic matter which allows Remnant to decay naturally.
- This property makes Tacetite exceptionally valuable as a material for crafting **weapons** used by Resonators against Tacet Discords — since the weapons can carry Remnant-infused destructive force.
- Tacetite is most commonly found in and around **Sonoro Spheres** and **Tacet Fields**, where Remnant Energy is sufficiently concentrated to crystallize into the substance.
- The **Black Shores** headquarters is built atop a massive formation of Tacetite, suggesting deliberate placement near a major source of frequency-active material.
- **Resonant Calcite** is a related substance that serves as an excellent conductor of Remnant Energy, used in various technological applications.

## Resonators: Humanity's Adapted Warriors

- **Resonators** are individuals who have developed the ability to **resonate with certain frequencies** in the world and manipulate them. Their emergence is one of the most significant developments in the Post-Lament era — they represent humanity's biological and spiritual adaptation to the chaos of the Lament.
- A Resonator undergoes a transformative event called an **Awakening** — triggered by a significant or defining life experience — during which they first resonate with the frequencies of something in the world and gain their **Resonance Ability**, also known as their **Forte**.
- At the moment of Awakening, a symbol called a **Tacet Mark** appears on the Resonator's body. Its exact shape is determined by their **Rabelle's Curve** — a complex biological and psychic curve unique to each individual. The placement of the mark on the body appears entirely random.
- The **Tacet Mark** is not static; it constantly changes in size and pulses in relation to the amount of Resonance Energy the Resonator currently holds. During a **Resonance Liberation**, the Mark glows intensely.
- Resonators are categorized by their Rabelle's Curve into three general types: **Natural** (awakening through gradual resonance), **Mutant** (awakening through unusual or traumatic circumstances), and **Congenital** (born with Resonance predispositions).
- Experts believe a Resonator's **past experiences and subconscious mind** directly influence what their Forte will be. Their genetic information also changes Post-Awakening, meaning Resonators are not merely skilled humans but genuinely altered beings.
- An extremely dangerous condition called **Overclocking** can occur when a Resonator's abilities spiral beyond their capacity to control — typically from external interference (such as Irideglow Crystal exposure) or extreme emotional stress.

## Resonators: The Pangu Terminal and Echo System

- The **Pangu Terminal** is a piece of technology carried by Resonators that serves as an interface with the world's frequency systems. Among its key functions is the ability to capture and reproduce the unique frequency emitted by a Tacet Discord ability.
- When a Tacet Discord is defeated, the remaining frequency does not immediately vanish. Through the Pangu Terminal's **Data Bank**, these lingering Reverberations can be transformed into **Echoes** — stable, usable frequency snapshots of the defeated Discord.
- Resonators can equip up to **five Echoes** simultaneously, with the first slot being the "Active" Echo — one that can be summoned to assist in combat, manifesting the Tacet Discord briefly. The remaining four slots provide passive enhancements to the Resonator's stats and abilities.
- Echoes amplify the Resonator's combat potential by infusing their abilities with the elemental frequencies and patterns of the Discords they have absorbed. This system represents humanity's mastery of repurposing the Lament's destructive energy for survival.
- There is a chance that, when a shattered Tacet Discord's Reverberation is processed, it will **leave behind a Reverberation effect** within the Terminal. This effect, once transformed into an Echo, carries the Discord's resonance pattern as a permanent combat tool.
